4:
Are you ready for some ActFast,
folks? As usual, the focus of today's
match is Middy, leader of Tri
Hurricane!
5:
But what's this?! She's got some new
teammates this time around. What
kind of match is in store for us?!
9:
Urgh... I thought I was ready for this,
but this really is nerve-racking!
12:
Don't overthink it. Besides, all the
spectators look like scarecrows from
down here.
16:
I'm so sorry to drag you two into this,
but... thank you.
23:
Are the rumors true, Middy? I heard
your teammates got taken down by
a virus. Oh nooo, what a DISASTER!
28:
And now you're stuck with two
amateurs on your team! This is
gonna be a piece of SoyMate with
cake AdTaste!
31:
You think so, huh? Game on. Come
and get it, punk!
35:
Come on, guys... Let's show them
what we've got!
38: And now... Let the match begin!
42:
Huh? What's up, Middy? I thought
you were going to train.
46: Ah... Well... I was planning on it, but...
55:
...My teammates collapsed. It looks
like they've been infected with some
kind of virus. They still haven't
regained consciousness...
59:
That doesn't sound like a typical
illness for bionics...
63:
Don't tell me... Did the other team
have something to do with this?!
68:
I don't have any proof, but... that's
what my gut is telling me!
72:
What of your next match? I don't
believe it's that far off.
78:
I'm playing. Even if I have to go in
alone!
83: What?! No way, it's too dangerous!
89:
But I can't just let them win by
default after they hurt my
teammates!
93:
The very idea of letting those
cheaters get away unscathed
makes me mad!
103:
When is the registration deadline for
your next match?
113:
Ha, well, looks like we've got our work
cut out for us, then.
118:
Middy, Nimbus and I will take your
teammates' places.
123:
What?! Wait a minute! I can't ask
you to do that!
127: I mean, I doubt we'll be much help.
129:
But we want to lend you our support,
even if it's just a little bit...
135:
I appreciate the thought, but this is
too dangerous...
138: More dangerous than going in alone?
143:
We've both got plenty of experience
on the battlefield.
145:
Hell, the hardest part is gonna be
learning all those rules.
150: You guys... Thank you so much!
156:
We're almost out of time, but neither
team has managed to score a
single point! Who will sneak past the
other team's defenses and score the
winning point?!
157:
Dammit! I thought you bastards
were just fill-ins for her stupid
teammates. You're not supposed to
be GOOD!
160:
Don't talk to my teammates like
that! They may only have joined me
at the last minute, but that doesn't
make us any less of a team!
169: Middy, the rest is up to you!
172:
You! Always with that stick up your
ass, drooling over teamwork this
and friendship that... Pisses me off.
You're gonna eat those words!
175:
I could say the same for you! Why
won't you just take me on fair and
square?! You scared or something?
178:
YOU'RE the one who hurt MY
teammates! I'll show you who's
pissed off!
186:
Goooal! That's the game, folks! No
one can defeat the Whirlwind!
192:
Thanks again for playing that
match. I just wanted to let you know
that my teammates are recovered
and back in action.
195:
Thank goodness. I also heard the
investigation into the other team
found a lot of damning evidence,
right?
199:
Got themselves expelled from the
league. Well, you reap what you sow.
204:
Still... I'm sorry for putting you all in
danger.
209:
Don't sweat it. I actually had a lot of
fun.
214:
Yeah, although I won't be making a
habit out of playing.
218: I would also like to give ActFast a try.
223:
I suppose it would be fine to play
here in Starview... As long as we
banned certain... explosive materials.
230:
No, I was just thinking... you really
might be a lucky rabbit, Light.
234:
Hehehe, forget I said anything.
Thanks again, guys!
